==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from French ''parvenu'', past participle of ''[[parvenir]]'', meaning "to arrive", learning borrowing from Latin ''[[pervenire]]'', from ''per-'' meaning "through" + ''venire'' meaning "to come."

===Noun===
'''parvenu'''
parvenu \PAR-vuh-noo; -nyoo\, noun:
#One that has recently or suddenly risen to a higher social or economic class but has not gained social acceptance of others in that class; an upstart.
#A person who has risen, climbed up, or has been promoted from his class, especially through acquisition of wealth, rights, or political authority.
#A person who has climbed the corporate ladder.
#A person who has risen to a higher place than original or customary.

adjective:
#Being a parvenu; also, like or having the characteristics of a parvenu.


